Two sentenced to die after arson killings | The Times
Two Muslim men have been sentenced to death after an arson attack and shootings in Xinjiang — an autonomous region of China — left 21 people dead.
Bloody even by the standards of a region prone to ethnic violence, the incident in Kashgar prefecture has caused months of tension. The region is already riven by an ethnic rivalry that regularly prompts clashes between indigenous Turkic Muslim Uighurs and Han Chinese migrants.
Anti-Han rioting by Uighurs in 2009 left 200 people dead in Urumqi, the capital of Xinjiang. Beijing tends to brand violence in the region as terrorism – a practice they use to

